The Long Walk Home;;1990;;PG;;Drama,History;;7.3;;Richard Pearce;;Sissy Spacek,Whoopi Goldberg,Dwight Schultz,Ving Rhames,Dylan Baker,Erika Alexander,Lexi Randall,Richard Habersham,Jason Weaver,Crystal Robbins,Cherene Snow,Chelcie Ross,Dan Butler,Philip Sterling,Schuyler Fisk,Nancy Moore Atchison,Haynes Brooke,Jim Aycock;;Dramatizes the events in 1955-1956 in Montgomery, Alabama, when blacks boycotted public transport because they were forced to sit at the back. Odessa works as a maid for the Thompsons, and as well as she is treated, she feels it is her duty to walk to work, even if it means she is exhausted, and gets to work late.;;https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0100046/